  "name": "Morrison VAD Hemolysis CFD — Minimal Credibility Package (W-ON-01)",
  "description": "This unit of assurance documents the credibility evidence for a CFD-based hemolysis prediction model of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump. The model has been applied in clinical research settings to inform hemolysis risk estimates for ventricular assist device candidates. Stress-based hemolysis indices were computed using a power-law damage accumulation model calibrated against in-vitro data. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across key rheological parameters. The assessment team determined that the model outputs are sufficiently credible for the stated engineering decision, and the package has been accepted under the minimal credibility profile. No structured context-of-use record is included in this package; intended-use scope is described only in this narrative.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-cfd-mrl5",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/hemolysis-index-acceptable-vad",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/fda-centrifugal-pump-cfd-v3",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-invitro-hemolysis-2021",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-piv-flowfield-2019"
  ],
